sequenceDiagram
    actor "React Client" as ReactClient
    participant "API/Web Layer" as APIWebLayer
    participant "Application Layer" as ApplicationLayer
    participant "Infrastructure Layer" as InfrastructureLayer

    activate APIWebLayer
    ReactClient->>APIWebLayer: 1. User submits credentials via Login form.
    APIWebLayer-->>ReactClient: Returns JWT on success or error response on failure.
    activate ApplicationLayer
    APIWebLayer->>ApplicationLayer: 2. Invokes authentication service with credentials DTO.
    ApplicationLayer-->>APIWebLayer: Returns AuthenticationResult object (Success/Failure/LockedOut).
    activate InfrastructureLayer
    ApplicationLayer->>InfrastructureLayer: 3. Find user by username using UserManager.
    InfrastructureLayer-->>ApplicationLayer: Returns User object or null if not found.
    ApplicationLayer->>ApplicationLayer: 4. Check if user account is locked.
    ApplicationLayer-->>ApplicationLayer: Boolean indicating locked status.
    ApplicationLayer->>InfrastructureLayer: 5. Validate password and handle lockout policy using SignInManager.
    InfrastructureLayer-->>ApplicationLayer: Returns SignInResult object.
    ApplicationLayer->>ApplicationLayer: 6. Log successful or failed login attempt to audit log.
    APIWebLayer->>APIWebLayer: 7. If authentication successful, generate signed JWT.
    APIWebLayer-->>APIWebLayer: Signed JWT string.

    note over ApplicationLayer: ASP.NET Core Identity's UserManager and SignInManager abstract away the direct database interacti...
    note over APIWebLayer: The generated JWT contains claims such as 'sub' (user ID), 'name', 'jti' (unique token ID), 'exp'...
    note over ReactClient: The React client must store the received JWT securely and include it in the 'Authorization: Beare...

    deactivate InfrastructureLayer
    deactivate ApplicationLayer
    deactivate APIWebLayer
